                            <comment id="15657195" author="eduard.tudenhoefner" created="Fri, 11 Nov 2016 14:29:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For testing we should probably be running &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/blob/master/internode_ssl_test.py#L7&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/blob/master/internode_ssl_test.py#L7&lt;/a&gt; with bootstrap=true&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15663906" author="pauloricardomg" created="Mon, 14 Nov 2016 13:26:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch that get rid of shuttting down socket input/output on &lt;tt&gt;ConnectionHandler&lt;/tt&gt;. This was a premature optimization not required for correctness, and I don&apos;t think it&apos;s worth it to keep it only for non-ssl to keep the code simple.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Added &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/pauloricardomg/cassandra-dtest/blob/8a16cc21e1d2bfc2c3f534b7f572e732b51c6b94/bootstrap_test.py#L119&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;simple bootstrap dtest with ssl&lt;/a&gt;, and verified that is fixed after this patch. Created cassandra-dtest &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/pull/1383&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;pull request&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch and test results available below:&lt;/p&gt;
